Cell.Text: You have reconsidered my offer, hmm? Onikaan kron?

[S] G|<<Shared>> Onikaan koraav gein miraad. It is wise to recognize when you only have one choice. | And you can trust me. Zu'u ni tahrodiis. Alduin has proven himself unworthy to rule. I go my own way now. | Free me, and I will carry you to Skuldafn.

Node.Caption: MQ303OdahviingIntroA1: Yes. I'll set you free if you promise to take me to Skuldafn.

Cell.Text: Zu'u ni tahrodiis. It was you that lured me here and took me prisoner... vobalaan grahmindol. I have done nothing to earn your distrust.

Node.Caption: MQ303OdahviingIntroA2: I'm still wondering if I can trust you.

Cell.Text: G|Hin aar, orin nu. And yet here I am, still your prisoner.

Node.Caption: MQ303OdahviingIntroB1: You did try to trick me into letting you go.

Cell.Text: [S] G|<<Shared>> Onikaan koraav gein miraad. It is wise to recognize when you only have one choice. | And you can trust me. Zu'u ni tahrodiis. Alduin has proven himself unworthy to rule. I go my own way now. | Free me, and I will carry you to Skuldafn.

Node.Caption: MQ303OdahviingIntroB2: I guess I'll have to trust you.

Cell.Text: Saraan uth - I await your command, as promised. Are you ready to see the world as only a dovah can?
[S] Zok brit uth! I warn you, once you've flown the skies of Keizaal, your envy of the dov will only increase.

Node.Caption: MQ303OdahviingFreeA1: I'm ready. Take me to Skuldafn.

Cell.Text: G|Kreh zini! The freedom of the sky beckons! Yet I stay here, nau gol, as promised.

Node.Caption: MQ303OdahviingFreeA2: Hold on. I'm not quite ready.

Cell.Text: You sure about that? You want to let that dragon loose after all the trouble to catch him in there?
[S] G|Your funeral. Someone else is gonna have to help you get him back in there again.
G|Hey, when you make up your mind, just let me know. I'll be here.
You will release me - ro laan - if in return I promise to take you to Skuldafn and stop helping Alduin?
